Package numerical.matrix

Class LSQRTester

java.lang.Object
numerical.matrix.LSQRTester
public class LSQRTester extends Object
Validation test of the LSQR matrix solution algorithm. This test uses data provided by LANL and should be treated as forbidden. The data files are contained in directory EMPSUtil.test.numerical.matrix.Data. This test loads the data, executes the LSQR.solve(...) function, and compares the returned results with that provided in the data directory.

Current results show exact agreement. Solution Time (sec) = 238.83382623 Output results (Calculated ... Input) ISTOP = 2 ... 2 ITN = 4618 ... 4618 ANORM = 9150.31034803221 ... 9150.310348032193 ACOND = 152022.3421284714 ... 152022.3421284711 RNORM = 151.84350702821376 ... 151.84350702821376 ARNORM = 13.882901116305009 ... 13.882901116305009 XNORM = 664.592180893012 ... 664.592180893012 Max Solution Difference = 0.0 Max Error Difference = 1.1102230246251565E-16

    • buildColumnSparseMatrix

      public ArrayList<SparseMatrixVector> buildColumnSparseMatrix(int ncols, ArrayList<SparseMatrixVector> rowSprs)
      Given the ArrayList aRowSprs for which each entry is a row in the matrix (row i is aRowSprs.get(i)) defined as a SparseMatrixVector, the transpose, aColSprs, can be constructed where each entry is a column in the matrix (column j is aColSprs.get(j)) also defined as a SparseMatrixVector. Each SparseMatrixVector (row) in aRowSprs contains the column index and value of all entries for that row. After construction, each SparseMatrixVector (column) in aColSprs contains the row index and value of all entries for that column.
